After Hartley fails on fake punt, Toledo Central Cath. responds with 9-yard TD run by Fields. PAT no good. Irish 20, Hawks 14, 7:12 in 3rd.
Here's an amazing stat: Hartley has 137 yards passing and 31 rushing at halftime. TCC run defense is stout, but Hawks have made big plays.
Halftime: Hartley 14, Toledo Central Catholic 14. TCC fumbled at Hawks 1 fighting for TD with 2:22 left.
Toledo CC matches Hartley with fourth down TD pass of its, a 21-yard strike from Durden to Swain. 14-14 now. What a high quality game.
On fourth and 7, Fleming completes a 36-yard TD pass to Phlllip Cole, giving Hartley a 14-7 lead. Hawks have passed for 139 yards.
Toledo Central Catholic answers with 35-yard TD pass from Durden to Blue. Capped a 65-yard drive. Hartley 7, TCC 7 with 5:32 in first Q.
One play after a Hartley 81-yard TD was negated by penalty, a screen from Anthony Carfagna to Nick Cone goes for 86-yard TD. Hawks 7-0.

Final score: New Albany 15, Reynoldsburg 13.
Gabe Philhower misses 42-yard FG try with 42 seconds left. New Albany takes over at own 10 and just needs to kneel on it.
New Albany forced to punt. Reynoldsburg has one more chance with ball at 20 with 2:29 left.
Reynoldsburg fumbles, New Albany recovers at Raiders 33. Eagles have it with 3:35, trying to hang on for win.
Reynoldsburg takes over at own 30 with 4:07 left, trailing 15-13.
Reynoldsburg was driving in for go-ahead score but fumbled at New Albany 10. Eagles still searching for first first down of second half.
Owusi-Antwi tips away 2-point conversion pass. New Albany leads 15-13 with 10:13 remaining in fourth.
Cowans-Wright scores on 15-yard run to pull Reynoldsburg deficit to 15-13. Raiders going for two-point conversion.
This has become a defensive standoff. New Albany leads Reynoldsburg 15-7 with 1:21 left in third.
Halftime: New Albany 15, Reynoldsburg 7. Eagles have 12 first downs to 3 for Raiders and hold huge lead in time of possession.
New Albany tacks on a safety on a dropped punt attempt in end zone. Eagles lead 15-7 with 5:10 left in half.
Reynoldsburg drives 65 yards for first TD, an 8-yard run by J'Vonte Edwards, early in second quarter. NA leads 13-7.
End first quarter: New Albany 13, Reynoldsburg 0. Eagles have eight first downs, Raiders zero.
A 27-yard FG by Zach Paragas gives New Albany a 13-0 lead over Reynoldsburg with 26 seconds left in first quarter.
After a three and out by Reynoldsburg, New Albany marches the field again and gets 22 FG by Zach Paragas. 10-0 Eagles.
